column5: I hope this works. These are the possibilities when you blend 6 inches of ice over 20+ feet of water and add a healthy smattering of Great Company. ALL DAY!!! Enjoy.  http://s956.photobuc...mview=slideshow    Sorry y'all. I'll try to resize and repost the pics.
Nice Eyes Moxie.  Keep Up The Good Work
Dude!!!!!! nice fish!!!!!
real nice eyes there
wow nice fish!
Healthy specimens you got there!
nice eyes??????  not one of you guy's were looking at his eye's you were all looking at his chest area, admit it.  by the way Moxie, nice fish in the pictures!
WOW !!!  You cant keep them that size up this way...
Moxie dude,  Real nice gut on those buggers.  Where abouts are you fishing? Those things are tanks compared to the eyes in my area.  Chad
Hawgs !
The Bay of Quinte. 8-10 lb fish are hit with regularity. The last fish in the Slide show was 10lbs-14oz. Truly amazing!
Wow great pics
SWEEEET !!!
awesome Post Moxie!  I get a lot of folks say the envy the fishing up here....well i envy BOQ!!!  More posts please
Wow, some real beauties there  Joey
That's unreal.   Looks like a great start to some great reports.
WOW!! what the heck eh?!?!  I need to get me some of dat.
Fantastic stuff! About how much ice were you on?

those are some real nice Wally's! I am debating going to Hay Bay tomorrow, or maybe another spot in the BOQ.. just wondering how thick the ice was out there, I heard there was lots of good ice in Hay Bay a few days ago, but this warm weather has me worried.  would you say ice was good enough to hold up to this warmer weather we have been having?

We were fishing in the reach on 5-7 inches of clear, black ice and if anyone is familiar with the area its a fairly narrow chute and draws quite the current. The run-off from the rain we are supposed to get will compromise the ice to a certain extent but by next weekend, given the below zero predictions I'm willing to bet it will tighten up again. Check as you go and be careful.   moxie.
Outstanding moxie BOQ's finest Leechman

Ice is sketchy all over that area after the rainfall. Might be a week or better before most areas are safe enough for foot travel. Best to check Quintefishingforums as the locals use the board to share info and such. Good luck and be careful out there.   Moxie
